ReciBEET

A team project created using MySQL, JavaScript, Node, Axios and Bootstrap.
ReciBeet is the perfect recipe finder for all things vegetarian! Leveraging the Spoonacular API, you can search for recipes by name or you can let us know whats already in your fridge or pantry and we will do the meal planning for you! Have an awesome family recipe? Utilize the create recipe function to have it saved and displayed for other users! Each user profile features both their saved and personally created recipes!

ReciBeet

Weather Five

A project utilizing the OpenWeather API, JavaScript, HTML, Bootstrap.
Do you know what the weather is going to be like in your city for the next five days? Me neither! With the help of the OpenWeather API, this project allows you to search for any cities weather and have your previous searches saved for quick easy access. Check out this awesome work in progress!

Weather Five
{/* /////////////////////////////////ROW THREE///////////////////////// */}

Beats and eats

A team build created using Spotify and Google Maps API, JavaScript, AJAX and Tailwind.
Curated for the hungriest of students, upon load the Google Maps API loads places near you to study, select your favorite tunes via genre and then look for food nearest you! You can search for food based off your latest craving or whatever the group is in the mood for! Not a fan of the song Spotify picked out for you? Need to pause the music to order food? The Spotify API call features all these functions and more.

Beats and Eats
